@{
    ViewBag.Title = "BookShelf-Manage your read, to read, and want to read bookshelf";
}
<img src="~/images/BookBanner.jpg" alt="book banner" action="" class="colorBanner img-fluid" />
<div class="container">

    <h1>Book Shelf</h1>
    <h2>Personal library management</h2>
    <p>
        The Bookshelf page is where each user can view and manage their personal
        collection of books. This section acts as a virtual library where books 
        are categorized by reading status: <em>To Read</em>, <em>Currently Reading</em>,
        and <em>Completed</em>.Users can add books from the Explore page or create custom entries for titles not yet in
        the system.
    </p>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <p>
        Each book on the shelf includes its title, author, genre, and user-defined rating.
        Users can update the reading status at any time, edit details, or remove books from the shelf.
        Books can also be tagged with custom notes or personal reflections, allowing readers to
        create a reading journal.
    </p>




    <div class="">
